  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The DR Congo&apos;s artisanal mining sector is a challenging context to work in, especially in eastern DR Congo, where Artisanal Small-scale Mines (ASM) are a driver of conflict and are often used by armed groups to exploit political, ethnic and historical tensions. In the province of Ituri, miners are poor and vulnerable and often ex-combatants or internally displaced people (IDPs) who have experienced high levels of trauma. ASMs selling to informal market creates an unreliable sources of income for miners and contributes to the fuelling of illicit activities. There exist numerous barriers to access legal markets for ASMs, such as heavy administrative requirements, high taxes, corruption, lack of connections and low levels of literacy.</narrative>
  </description>
